      "message": "Thanks Manoj — your point is well taken - bmcweb reads interfaces via the mapper, not paths, so the Redfish Chassis collection claim in my commit message was incorrect. And your broader point about D-Bus paths being opaque identifiers -- as entity-manager implements it -- is the right architectural principle.        The change that actually addresses bmcweb\u0027s Chassis enumeration is the interface\nrefactor in 89127 (Inventory.Item.Accelerator for GPU, Inventory.Item.Cpu for Processor, etc.). I\u0027m abandoning this path-rearrangement change, rebasing 89127 to stand alone on master, and updating its commit message to make the interface-level\nmotivation explicit. Thanks for pushing back on this.",
